  "calibration_note": "SCAN TRIGGER CORRECTION plus MEASUREMENT GAP. First, a data-quality note the reviewer needs: the 2026-07-20 scan attributed a Middleton, Wisconsin layoff to Thermo Fisher Scientific. That appears to be a misattribution — the Middleton closure in that period belongs to Sun Nuclear Corp., a Mirion Medical company. The scan's underlying claim about a Thermo Fisher restructuring pattern is nonetheless correct, just sourced to the wrong site; the verified events are Weaverville/Asheville NC (421 employees), Franklin MA, and Princeton NJ (113 employees). Second, Thermo Fisher has never been individually assessed and its published 60.9 is a bulk-import placeholder with a near-flat 3.5. The -12.1 gap is largely that arithmetic difference, consistent with the documented scrutiny bias. The verified conduct — repeated site closures with 12 to 24 months of WARN notice, alongside a substantial CSR programme — does not describe an institution that fell 12 points. Recommendation is flag-for-review for cohort calibration, not a conduct-based downgrade.",
